    "Considere el siguiente problema: Hallar $u=u(x,y)$, satisfaciendo:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{\\partial^2 u}{\\partial x^2} + \\dfrac{\\partial^2 u}{\\partial y^2} + 2\\pi^2 \\sin(\\pi x)\\sin(\\pi y) = 0$$\n",
    "sobre $\\Omega = (1,0)\\times(1,0)$, y con la condición $u=0$ sobre todo el borde de $\\Omega$. \n",
    "\n",
    "La solucion del problema anterior viene dada por:\n",
    "$$u(x,y) = \\sin(\\pi x)\\sin(\\pi y).$$ "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "4d01077f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def f_np(x,y):\n",
    "    '''Función fuente para la ecuación de Poisson.'''\n",
    "    return 2*np.pi**2 * np.sin(np.pi*x)*np.sin(np.pi*y)\n",
    "\n",
    "def f_th(x,y):\n",
    "    '''Función fuente para la ecuación de Poisson.'''\n",
    "    return 2*torch.pi**2 * torch.sin(torch.pi*x)*torch.sin(torch.pi*y)"
   ]
  },
